    stem: "An 8-year-old child presents after a near-drowning incident in a swimming pool. He was submerged for approximately 2 minutes. On arrival, he is coughing, SpO2 is 91% on room air, and chest X-ray shows bilateral patchy infiltrates. What is the minimum recommended observation period?",
