    stem: "A 7-year-old child presents with periorbital edema, dark-colored urine, and hypertension (BP 142/94 mmHg). He had a streptococcal pharyngitis infection 3 weeks ago. Urinalysis shows hematuria and proteinuria. What condition should the emergency nurse suspect?",
